import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts()
    target_counts = data['target'].value_counts()
    
    ax1 = plt.gca()
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    
    ax1.bar(source_counts.index, source_counts.values, alpha=0.5, label='Source')
    ax2.bar(target_counts.index, target_counts.values, alpha=0.5, label='Target', color='orange')
    
    ax1.set_ylabel('Source Count')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Target Count')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax1.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        ax2.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.setp(ax1.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.setp(ax2.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    
    ax1.legend(loc='upper left')
    ax2.legend(loc='upper right')
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of source and target in the dataset?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    source_target_counts = data.groupby(['source', 'target']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
    sns.heatmap(source_target_counts, cmap='viridis', annot=True, fmt='d')
    plt.title("What is the most common source and target combination in the dataset?")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_targets_per_source = data.groupby('source')['target'].count().mean()
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts()
    source_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    plt.axhline(avg_targets_per_source, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_targets_per_source:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average number of targets per source in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    unique_sources = data['source'].nunique()
    unique_targets = data['target'].nunique()
    sizes = [unique_sources, unique_targets]
    labels = ['Unique Sources', 'Unique Targets']
    
    plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.axis('equal')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique sources and targets in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
